history.content: 170 and 161 are probably the hardest, and 168 isn't too bad from what I've heard. Depends a lot on your study habits and past classes but it seems manageable. If you end up with both 161 and 170 it might be a little on the harder side of things.

children.subject:
I haven't taken 170 but I hear the problem sets are quite long. I have taken the other three and I'd say the workload for those is 161 > 186 > 168.

If the workload is similar to what it has been this past year, in each class you can expect:

161: two midterms, a final, 3-4 (relatively short) problem sets, 2 (relatively short) projects, and 1 longer "design" project

186: two midterms, a final, ~bi-weekly quizzes (very short and pretty much guaranteed 100% if you do them), and 5 programming assignments (1 SQL and the rest in Java)

168: one midterm, a final, and three pretty short networking-related python programming projects

history.content: I will take 170, and choose two from the other three. How's the workload?
